text:
Hi, 

The ErrorDocument has a case sensitive option "default", which conflicts with the case insensitivity of Apache's configuration design. According to my understanding, httpd champions case insensitivity for both configuration directive and configuration options.

The fix is straightforward as follows:

--- server/core.c	2012-11-28 12:57:48.599129124 -0800
+++ server/core.c	2013-01-14 21:02:01.601358837 -0800
@@ -1497,7 +1497,7 @@
                             RESPONSE_CODES);
         }

-        if (strcmp(msg, "default") == 0) {
+        if (strcasecmp(msg, "default") == 0) {
             /* special case: ErrorDocument 404 default restores the
              * canned server error response
              */
